In this lesson, we'll explore what kind of language should be used when writing a cover letter.
_________________________________________________________________________________
<strong>Language of a Cover Letter</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>In general, the words you should choose for your cover letter are similar to those for a resume!
<ul>
 	<li>The major difference is that cover letters should be written in <strong>complete sentences</strong>!</li>
</ul>
</li>
 	<li>Do you remember from the resume lessons how you should phrase your accomplishments as transferable skills? Here’s a reminder!<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-44314" src="http://p2i.pyd.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Language-of-a-Cover-Letter-Graphic-3b.png" alt="language-of-a-cover-letter-graphic-3b" width="889" height="184" /></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;
_________________________________________________________________________________
It is also still important to be <strong>concise </strong>in a cover letter, even though you are using complete sentences! Here is a reminder of what concise means:

Remember while you are writing that it’s important to have a strong vocabulary! A <strong>thesaurus </strong>can be helpful in this case also.

<em>Remember, don’t use any words or language that you couldn’t use while speaking! You want to sound like yourself, but still be professional!</em>
_________________________________________________________________________________
<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-44318" src="http://p2i.pyd.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/cover-letters-review-activity-3b.png" alt="cover-letters-review-activity-3b" width="493" height="510" />

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Remember, a cover letter is used to:
<ul>
 	<li>Introduce yourself</li>
 	<li>Invite an employer to read your resume</li>
 	<li>Highlight some of the most important qualities from your resume</li>
 	<li>Request an interview</li>
</ul>
<strong><u>Cover Letter Salutations</u></strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Circle the greeting you would choose for “Susan Jones”</li>
</ol>
Dear Mr./Ms./Mrs. Jones,
<ol start="2">
 	<li>Circle the greeting you would choose for “Daniel Keller”</li>
</ol>
Dear Mr./Ms./Mrs. Keller,
<ol start="3">
 	<li>Circle the greeting you would choose for “Pat O’Brien”</li>
</ol>
Dear Mr./Ms./Mrs. O’Brien,

What if you don’t know the name of the hiring manager?<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-44320" src="http://p2i.pyd.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/face-graphic-coer-letters-3b-e1515987655321.png" alt="face-graphic-coer-letters-3b" width="150" height="210" />
<ol>
 	<li>Try contacting the company to find out the name of who will be reading your letter.
<ol>
 	<li>Use a search engine</li>
 	<li>Call the company</li>
</ol>
</li>
 	<li>If you still can’t find a name, your greeting should be:</li>
</ol>
“_______________________________________________________”

